== Mudball buffer module ==

The buffer module is a thin wrapper around the PHP output buffering library, it is for:

* starting buffers
* clearing buffers
* flushing buffers

=== mud_buffer_reset() ===

This will clear all open buffers and start a new one.

=== mud_buffer_start() ===

This will push a new buffer onto the buffers stack.

=== mud_buffer_flush() ===

This will flush the current buffer and then pop it from the stack.

=== mud_buffer_clear() ===

This will delete the current buffer.

=== mud_buffer_clear_all() ===

This will delete all open buffers.
